---
description: Short JSDoc on every exported function, class, and public method; link third-party APIs
globs: src/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# Public symbol documentation

Every **exported** function, class, interface, and **public** method (not `private` / `#`) must have a JSDoc block directly above it.

## Length

- **At most 3 lines** of description (not counting `@param` / `@returns` / `@see`).
- **Prefer 2 lines** — one for purpose, one for non-obvious behavior or constraints.
- No filler (“This function…”, “Handles the…”); state *what* and *when* it matters.

## Third-party resources

When code calls an external HTTP API, SDK, relay, or model provider, the doc **must** include links:

1. **Official API/docs URL** (the provider’s public reference).
2. **Project integration doc** under `docs/3rd-parties/` when one exists.

Use `@see` for links. Keep the description short; put URLs in `@see`, not inline prose walls.

| Integration | Project doc | Official docs |
|-------------|-------------|---------------|
| X | `docs/3rd-parties/twitter-x-dot-com.md` | https://docs.x.com/ |
| Finnhub | `docs/3rd-parties/finhub.md` | https://finnhub.io/docs/api |
| Nostr | `docs/3rd-parties/nostr.md` | (relay / NIP docs as appropriate) |
| Replicate | `docs/3rd-parties/replicate-ai.md` | https://replicate.com/docs |

If you add a new third-party integration, add or update its row in `docs/3rd-parties/` and link it from the service doc.

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — no doc on exported class or public method
export class XService implements ISocialService {
  async postMessage(message: string): Promise<PostMessageResponse> { ... }
}

// ✅ GOOD — short description + @see for external API
/**
 * Posts plain text to X via API v2.
 * Refreshes OAuth2 tokens on 401 and retries once.
 *
 * @see https://docs.x.com/
 * @see docs/3rd-parties/twitter-x-dot-com.md
 */
async postMessage(message: string): Promise<PostMessageResponse> { ... }

// ✅ GOOD — internal module, no third party (2 lines, no @see required)
/**
 * Fans out a message to every registered social target.
 * Uses allSettled so one failure does not block others.
 */
export async function fanOut(message: string): Promise<void> { ... }

// ❌ BAD — essay, no links on X API usage
/**
 * This method is responsible for posting messages to the X platform.
 * It uses axios and handles errors and token refresh in various cases...
 */
```

## Scope

- **Required:** `export` functions, classes, interfaces; public methods on exported classes.
- **Optional:** `private` helpers, file-local functions, one-liner route wiring in `routes.ts`.
- Do not document obvious getters/setters unless behavior is non-obvious.
